items.title: LIVE: House votes on plan to prevent a government shutdown
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Watch live as the House votes on a plan to prevent a government shutdown.

House Speaker Mike Johnson proposed a new plan that would temporarily fund federal operations and disaster aid, but punted President-elect Donald Trump’s demands for a debt limit increase into the new year.

House Republicans have been meeting behind closed doors on next steps after Trump doubled down on his insistence that a debt ceiling increase be included in any deal — and if not, he said in an early morning post, let the closures “start now.”

items.title: LIVE: View from Magdeburg after suspected attack in Germany
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Live from Magdeburg, Germany, after a driver plowed into a busy outdoor Christmas market on Friday, killing at least two people and injuring at least 68 others in what authorities suspect was an attack.

The driver of the car was arrested, German news agency dpa reported, citing unidentified government officials in the state of Saxony-Anhalt.

#news #germany #magdeburg #live

items.title: LIVE: Amazon workers strike in Queens, New York
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Live from Queens, New York, as Amazon workers affiliated with the Teamsters union launched a strike at seven of the company’s delivery hubs less than a week before Christmas.

The Teamsters said the workers, who voted to authorize strikes in recent days, joined picket lines after Amazon ignored a Sunday deadline the union had set for contract negotiations.

#amazon #news #live
